        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pine nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Once toasted, transfer them to a bowl and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pine nuts are toasting, halve the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>sun-dried tomato paste </strong>and <strong>coconut yoghurt</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> sun-dried tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sun-dried tomato stock</strong>, <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>quick-cook amorini </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook, covered, for an initial 2 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained cannellini beans</strong> and <strong>washed</strong> <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and stir it all together</p><p>Cook, covered, for 3 min further or until the pasta is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-sun-dried-tomato-pasta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato pasta </strong>and garnish with the <strong>pine nuts</strong></p><p>Drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
